> Cook it once, eat it twice: tonight's dinner extras transform into tomorrow's lunch. That's thanks to special added ingredients that can easily be heated up, even at the office (your coworkers will be amazed, trust us). For the first meal, you'll dive right into a mash-up of Korean and Mexican cuisines with tacos filled with chicken and cabbage in a bulgogi sauce. The next day, the meat is added to a stir-fry with peppers over rice.

== Dinner: Korean Chicken Tacos ==

Wash and dry all produce. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{4%units}, separating whites from greens. Core, deseed, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1%unit} and @long green pepper{1%unit}. Halve @lime{1%unit}, cutting one half into wedges.

Bring 1 cup water and a pinch of @salt{pinch} to boil in a #small pot{}. Once boiling, stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}. Lower heat to a gentle simmer and cover. Cook until tender, ~{12-14%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until you're ready to pack lunch.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine juice from lime half and @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Stir in half the scallion whites and a quarter of the @shredded red cabbage{4%oz}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside, tossing every now and then.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tbsp} and @sriracha{3%tsp}(to taste). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture has a drizzling consistency.

Pat @chicken breast strips{20%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @moo shu spice blend{1%tsp}.

  Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{5%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add chicken and cook, stirring, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-7%minutes}. Turn off heat; remove chicken from pan and set aside. Wipe out pan with paper towels.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add bell and green peppers. Cook, tossing, until softened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Toss in remaining scallion whites and cook ~{1%minute} more.

Stir in half the chicken, @hoisin sauce{2%tbsp}, @soy sauce{2%tbsp}, and @butter{2%tbsp}. Transfer mixture to a #large bowl{} and set aside until you're ready to pack lunch. Wipe out pan with a #paper towel{}. Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat.

Add rest of cabbage to pan. Cook, tossing, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Squeeze in juice of 1 lime wedge. Reduce heat to low, then stir in @bulgogi sauce{4%oz} and remaining chicken.

Remove pan from heat. Wrap @flour tortillas{6%units} in a moist paper towel. Microwave on high until warm, about ~{1%minute}.

Fill tortillas with bulgogi chicken. Garnish with slaw, then drizzle with crema and any leftover sriracha (to taste). Garnish with half the scallion greens. Serve with remaining lime wedges.

== Lunch: Chicken Stir-Fry ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and divide between reusable #containers{}. Arrange chicken stir-fry next to rice and sprinkle with remaining scallion greens. Keep refrigerated until ready to eat. Microwave on high for ~{1-2%minutes} before enjoying.